column9: FlavorText
Traditional meals are cooked in a great fire-stone pit.\r\nIn a crisis, those stones can pull double duty.
The fruit of the volcanic nightshade plant can leave veteran warriors in tears.
The Ngamahu Tribe believes the Karui will be reforged in a volcano at the end of time.
When Ngamahu's chosen truly wish to destroy an enemy, nothing can stop them.
Hunters of the Tasalio Tribe are just as effective on land.
They slip through shadows of their own making.
A clear day dawns only for the lucky.
Tasalio bids you take a moment to stop and enjoy the calm of the ocean.
Arohongui looks after all those in need.
The never-ending journey must be walked alone.
The lunar plains are cold, but the silver palace is always warm and welcoming.
Winter is inevitable, but so is the spring.
Valako's gifts are unpredictable, but welcome.
An arrow in a storm may lose its course, but it will bring death where it eventually falls.
Passed down through the generations, they protect those who seek Valako's grace.
Only a fool fights the tide.
With each new life, the entire tribe is invigorated.
The end of Time is also its beginning.
Hinekora is not the master of Death, but she is its Mother.
There is no use trying to escape destiny.
Though you might not see it, the forest is always growing.
That which is wounded may become whole again in time.
Life springs from death in a grand cycle.
Tawhoa gifted humanity the ability to dream, so that they may aspire to greater things.
\"The Oriathans have generously provided us with a banquet!\"
\"If you waver, drink of my blood, and fight on!\"
\"Bite down upon your master's throat, and die before you let go!\"
\"The guards will have no rest this night. When they tire, we strike...\"
The Sun chases the Moon across the sky, thirsting for a momentary touch.
Her courage was contagious.
Let us graciously allow the enemy to fight in the shade.
Clever archers always have a trick in reserve.
The warriors of the Tukohama Tribe call the brink of death home.
Ancestral wood splinters freely under the heavy weight of jade.
The fire in the blood is like no other thrill.
A true warrior is never unarmed.
Slow and steady wins the race.
\"Get out of my way!\"
Simple, but effective.
Rongokurai gifts his strength to protect the weak.
Remember the days that were not so grim and cold as today.
The long chew is half the satisfaction.
For enemies you do not respect.
If you hear the call, you must answer.
A blessing upon all those trees touched by the sacred spirit.
